President Obama commends the bipartisan majority of Senators for confirming John Koskinen as the next commissioner of the Internal Revenue Service (IRS). Koskinen has extensive experience in both the private and public sectors, including leading institutions during difficult times. The President praises Koskinen's unwavering integrity and believes his strong leadership and expertise make him the ideal person to lead the IRS. President Obama also expresses gratitude to Daniel Werfel for his exceptional service as principal deputy commissioner and looks forward to working with Koskinen in his new role.